  <h2>What is Artificial Intelligence (AI)?</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Artificial Intelligence</strong> — or <strong>AI</strong> — is the ability of a computer or machine to <em>think, learn, and make decisions</em> in ways that seem almost human. The word "artificial" means made by people, and "intelligence" means the ability to learn and understand.
  </p>
  <p>
    AI isn't magic or science fiction — it's real technology that you probably use every single day without even realising it! When you ask Siri a question, get a YouTube recommendation, or your phone recognises your face to unlock — that's AI at work!
  </p>

  <blockquote>
    AI is teaching computers to learn from experience — just like how you get better at football the more you practice!
  </blockquote>

  <h2>AI in Everyday Life</h2>
  <p>AI is already everywhere around you. Here are examples you might recognise:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>🎵 <strong>Music Recommendations</strong> — Spotify and YouTube suggest songs and videos you'll like based on what you've listened to before.</li>
    <li>📸 <strong>Face Recognition</strong> — Your phone recognises your face to unlock. Photo apps group pictures of the same person together.</li>
    <li>🗣️ <strong>Voice Assistants</strong> — Siri (Apple), Alexa (Amazon), and Google Assistant understand your voice and answer questions.</li>
    <li>🎮 <strong>Game AI</strong> — The enemies and characters in video games use AI to react to your moves intelligently.</li>
    <li>🚗 <strong>Self-Driving Cars</strong> — Tesla's autopilot uses AI to drive the car, avoid obstacles, and navigate routes.</li>
    <li>🤖 <strong>ChatGPT</strong> — An AI that can write essays, answer questions, code, and have conversations!</li>
    <li>📧 <strong>Spam Filters</strong> — Your email's spam folder is filled by AI that detects junk mail.</li>
    <li>🏥 <strong>Medical Diagnosis</strong> — AI helps doctors detect cancer from X-rays and scans more accurately.</li>
    <li>🛍️ <strong>Shopping Recommendations</strong> — "You might also like..." on Amazon uses AI.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How Does AI Learn? — Machine Learning</h2>
  <p>
    Traditional programs follow exact instructions written by programmers. AI is different — it can <strong>learn from data</strong>! This is called <strong>Machine Learning (ML)</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>Here's how machine learning works:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>📚 <strong>Training</strong> — You feed the AI thousands (or millions!) of examples. Example: Show an AI 10,000 photos labelled "cat" and 10,000 labelled "dog."</li>
    <li>🔍 <strong>Pattern Finding</strong> — The AI finds patterns in the data. "Cats have pointy ears and whiskers. Dogs have floppy ears and bigger noses."</li>
    <li>🧪 <strong>Testing</strong> — You show the AI new photos it has never seen and ask: "Is this a cat or dog?"</li>
    <li>✅ <strong>Improving</strong> — When the AI gets it wrong, it adjusts and tries again. Over time, it becomes very accurate!</li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    Machine learning is like teaching a toddler what a dog is by showing them hundreds of dog pictures. After enough examples, they can recognise any dog — even one they've never seen before!
  </blockquote>

  <h2>What are Neural Networks?</h2>
  <p>
    The most powerful kind of machine learning uses <strong>neural networks</strong> — computer systems inspired by how the human brain works!
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>🧠 Your brain is made of billions of connected cells called <strong>neurons</strong>. They pass electrical signals to each other.</li>
    <li>💻 An <strong>artificial neural network</strong> mimics this with <em>virtual neurons</em> (numbers and maths) connected in layers.</li>
    <li>📥 <strong>Input Layer</strong> — Receives the data (e.g., pixels of an image).</li>
    <li>🔄 <strong>Hidden Layers</strong> — Many layers of "neurons" that process and find patterns in the data.</li>
    <li>📤 <strong>Output Layer</strong> — Gives the answer (e.g., "This is a cat with 98% confidence").</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Deep Learning</strong> is when you use neural networks with many hidden layers. It's what powers face recognition, image generation, and ChatGPT!
  </p>

  <h2>Types of AI</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>🤖 <strong>Narrow AI (Weak AI)</strong> — AI designed for ONE specific task. Examples: chess-playing AI, spam filters, face recognition. This is the only kind of AI that exists today!</li>
    <li>🧠 <strong>General AI (Strong AI)</strong> — Hypothetical AI that could do <em>any</em> intellectual task a human can. This doesn't exist yet.</li>
    <li>🚀 <strong>Super AI</strong> — Hypothetical AI that surpasses human intelligence in every way. Only in science fiction (for now!).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>AI and Creativity</h2>
  <p>
    Amazingly, AI isn't just for maths and logic — it can be creative too!
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>🎨 <strong>AI Art</strong> — Tools like DALL-E and Midjourney can generate stunning artwork from text descriptions. "A cat astronaut floating in space" → amazing image in seconds!</li>
    <li>🎵 <strong>AI Music</strong> — AI can compose original music in any style — jazz, pop, classical — just by learning from thousands of songs.</li>
    <li>✍️ <strong>AI Writing</strong> — ChatGPT can write stories, poems, essays, jokes, and code!</li>
    <li>🎬 <strong>AI Video</strong> — AI can generate realistic videos and deepfakes from just text or a photo.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Is AI Always Right?</h2>
  <p>
    No! AI makes mistakes — sometimes big ones. Here's why:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>📊 <strong>Biased Data</strong> — If the training data is unfair or biased, the AI learns those biases too.</li>
    <li>🎭 <strong>Hallucinations</strong> — AI language models (like ChatGPT) sometimes confidently say wrong things! Always verify AI answers.</li>
    <li>🆕 <strong>New Situations</strong> — AI struggles with completely new situations it wasn't trained on.</li>
    <li>🤔 <strong>No Common Sense</strong> — AI doesn't truly understand the world — it only finds patterns.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Can AI Replace Humans?</h2>
  <p>
    AI is changing many jobs — but it also creates new ones! Here's the balanced view:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>🔄 Some repetitive jobs (like data entry or sorting) may be automated by AI.</li>
    <li>🆕 New jobs are being created: AI trainer, prompt engineer, AI ethics officer, data scientist.</li>
    <li>🤝 Most experts think AI will be a <em>tool that helps humans</em> — not replace them entirely.</li>
    <li>💡 Skills like creativity, empathy, critical thinking, and leadership are things AI can't fully replicate.</li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    AI is a very powerful tool — like a hammer. Hammers don't replace builders; they help them build better, faster!
  </blockquote>

  <h2>The History of AI</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>📅 <strong>1950</strong> — Alan Turing asks "Can machines think?" and invents the Turing Test.</li>
    <li>📅 <strong>1956</strong> — The term "Artificial Intelligence" is coined at a conference at Dartmouth College.</li>
    <li>♟️ <strong>1997</strong> — IBM's Deep Blue chess computer beats world champion Garry Kasparov!</li>
    <li>🎮 <strong>2011</strong> — IBM's Watson wins Jeopardy! against human champions.</li>
    <li>🎨 <strong>2015</strong> — DeepMind's AlphaGo defeats the world champion at the complex board game Go.</li>
    <li>🤖 <strong>2022</strong> — ChatGPT is released and reaches 100 million users in just 2 months — the fastest growing app ever!</li>
    <li>🚀 <strong>Today</strong> — AI is advancing faster than at any point in history!</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Fun Facts About AI</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>🤯 GPT-4 (the AI behind ChatGPT) was trained on over <strong>45 terabytes</strong> of text from the Internet!</li>
    <li>⚡ AI can analyse a medical X-ray scan in <strong>under 1 second</strong> — and sometimes spot cancer that human doctors miss.</li>
    <li>🌍 AI is helping scientists discover new medicines, predict earthquakes, and fight climate change.</li>
    <li>🎮 The AI in modern video games can adapt its strategy based on how you play!</li>
    <li>🔬 Scientists are using AI to <strong>fold proteins</strong> — solving a 50-year-old biology mystery in just one day.</li>
  </ul>

